v.
HEALTH NETWORK SOLUTIONS, INC. f/k/a Chiropractic Network of the Carolinas, Inc. ; Michael Binder; Steven Binder ; Robert Stroud, Jr.; Larry Grosman; Matthew Schmid ; Ralph Ransone; Jeffrey K. Baldwin ; Ira Rubin ; Richard Armstrong; Brad Batchelor; John Smith; Rick Jackson; and Mark Hooper No. 251PA18 Supreme Court of North Carolina. August 14, 2019 Robert E. Fields, III, Attorney at Law, for Sykes, Susan, et al. Samuel Pinero, II, Attorney at Law, for Sykes, Susan, et al. William A. Blancato, GAL Appellate Attorney, for Sykes, Susan, et al. Leon E. Porter, Attorney at Law, Winston-Salem, for Sykes, Susan, et al. Ellis B. Drew, III, Attorney at Law, Winston-Salem. Jennifer K. Van Zant, Attorney at Law, Greensboro, for Health Network Solutions, Inc., et al. Benjamin R. Norman, Attorney at Law, Greensboro, for Health Network Solutions, Inc., et al. W. Michael Dowling, Attorney at Law, for Health Network Solutions, Inc., et al.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed by Plaintiffs on the 16th of July 2019 for rehearing of the decision of this Court pursuant to Rule 31, N.C. Rules of Appellate Procedure, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the North Carolina Court of Appeals:

"Denied by order of the Court in conference, this the 14th of August 2019."
